text: carbs are not the enemy carbs can be
your best friend if you eat them at the
right time of the day in the right

we are able to utilize carbohydrates for

early part of the day and there have
been some amazing fascinating studies
out of Israel where they've actually
tested this and they've given two groups
of overweight women the exact same
number of calories and the exact same
foods on the diet but the difference is
how they distributed their calories and
carbs throughout the day a group of
women who ate most of their calories and
carbs at breakfast and lunch and have
these super tiny low-carb dinners lost
two and a half times more weight had two
inches more weight loss around their
waist and had lower triglycerides after
a three-month period compared to a group
of women who ate the same exact calories
same exact foods in an opposite pattern
where they had a really tiny low-carb
breakfast and a very large high carb
dinner and so we really understand that
it's not just how many carbs you eat
total and how many calories you eat
total but when you eat your calories and
when you eat your carbs matters a lot
